hashCode() - Method in class piskorski.util.set.SimpleIntSet
Overwrites the standard native hashCode() method from java.lang.Object, since it (usually) returns the internal memory address for this object (which does not suffice in our case, viz., using the data vectors as keys in a hash table and checking for structural equality); The code is borrowed from java.lang.String; the hash code for a data vector is computed as code[0]*31^(n-1) + code[1]*31^(n-2) + ...
